        "title": "How to Scroll to some particular textview element using soothscroll?",
        "body": "<p>In my page I have two parts. One is drop down which contains multiple categories. And other one contains products of all categories. Like I showed in image. When user Clicking any category then the page get scroll to the appropriate products of choosed category.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Up to now I have tried<\/strong>:-\nFirst of all, I need to bind dynamically Category names in the spinner. After that I need to bind the products with the Category name having the id of spinner's value. So, when user choosing anything I need to get the value from the spinner and after that I need to match that value with the products elements. Once it get matched then my page should scroll to that particular element. For this anybody having any idea?<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/P6UeX.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">enter image description here<\/a><\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 58281207,
